57/*
58 * Like printf, only we append to a buffer.
59 */
60protected int
61file_vprintf(struct magic_set *ms, const char *fmt, va_list ap)
62{
63 int len;
64 char *buf, *newstr;
65
66 if (ms->event_flags & EVENT_HAD_ERR)
67 return 0;
68 len = vasprintf(&buf, fmt, ap);
69 if (len < 0)
70 goto out;
71
72 if (ms->o.buf != NULL) {
73 len = asprintf(&newstr, "%s%s", ms->o.buf, buf);
74 free(buf);
75 if (len < 0)
76 goto out;
77 free(ms->o.buf);
78 buf = newstr;
79 }
80 ms->o.buf = buf;
81 return 0;
82out:
83 fprintf(stderr, "vasprintf failed (%s)", strerror(errno));
84 return -1;
85}
86
87protected int
88file_printf(struct magic_set *ms, const char *fmt, ...)
89{
90 int rv;
91 va_list ap;
92
93 va_start(ap, fmt);
94 rv = file_vprintf(ms, fmt, ap);
95 va_end(ap);
96 return rv;
97}
98
99/*
100 * error - print best error message possible
101 */
102/*VARARGS*/
103__attribute__((__format__(__printf__, 3, 0)))
104private void
105file_error_core(struct magic_set *ms, int error, const char *f, va_list va,
106 size_t lineno)
107{
108 /* Only the first error is ok */
109 if (ms->event_flags & EVENT_HAD_ERR)
110 return;
111 if (lineno != 0) {
112 free(ms->o.buf);
113 ms->o.buf = NULL;
114 (void)file_printf(ms, "line %" SIZE_T_FORMAT "u:", lineno);
115 }
116 if (ms->o.buf && *ms->o.buf)
117 (void)file_printf(ms, " ");
118 (void)file_vprintf(ms, f, va);
119 if (error > 0)
120 (void)file_printf(ms, " (%s)", strerror(error));
121 ms->event_flags |= EVENT_HAD_ERR;
122 ms->error = error;
123}
124
125/*VARARGS*/
126protected void
127file_error(struct magic_set *ms, int error, const char *f, ...)
128{
129 va_list va;
130 va_start(va, f);
131 file_error_core(ms, error, f, va, 0);
132 va_end(va);
133}
134
135/*
136 * Print an error with magic line number.
137 */
138/*VARARGS*/
139protected void
140file_magerror(struct magic_set *ms, const char *f, ...)
141{
142 va_list va;
143 va_start(va, f);
144 file_error_core(ms, 0, f, va, ms->line);
145 va_end(va);
146}
147
148protected void
149file_oomem(struct magic_set *ms, size_t len)
150{
151 file_error(ms, errno, "cannot allocate %" SIZE_T_FORMAT "u bytes",
152 len);
153}
154
155protected void
156file_badseek(struct magic_set *ms)
157{
158 file_error(ms, errno, "error seeking");
159}
160
161protected void
162file_badread(struct magic_set *ms)
163{
164 file_error(ms, errno, "error reading");
165}

169protected int
170file_separator(struct magic_set *ms)
171{
172 return file_printf(ms, "\n- ");
173}
174
175static int
176checkdone(struct magic_set *ms, int *rv)
177{
178 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_CONTINUE) == 0)
179 return 1;
180 if (file_separator(ms) == -1)
181 *rv = -1;
182 return 0;
183}
184
185protected int
186file_default(struct magic_set *ms, size_t nb)
187{
188 if (ms->flags & MAGIC_MIME) {
189 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_MIME_TYPE) &&
190 file_printf(ms, "application/%s",
191 nb ? "octet-stream" : "x-empty") == -1)
192 return -1;
193 return 1;
194 }
195 if (ms->flags & MAGIC_APPLE) {
196 if (file_printf(ms, "UNKNUNKN") == -1)
197 return -1;
198 return 1;
199 }
200 if (ms->flags & MAGIC_EXTENSION) {
201 if (file_printf(ms, "???") == -1)
202 return -1;
203 return 1;
204 }
205 return 0;
206}

208/*
209 * The magic detection functions return:
210 * 1: found
211 * 0: not found
212 * -1: error
213 */
214/*ARGSUSED*/
215protected int
216file_buffer(struct magic_set *ms, int fd, struct stat *st,
217 const char *inname __attribute__ ((__unused__)),
218 const void *buf, size_t nb)
219{
220 int m = 0, rv = 0, looks_text = 0;
221 const char *code = NULL;
222 const char *code_mime = "binary";
223 const char *def = "data";
224 const char *ftype = NULL;
225 char *rbuf = NULL;
226 struct buffer b;
227
228 buffer_init(&b, fd, st, buf, nb);
229 ms->mode = b.st.st_mode;
230
231 if (nb == 0) {
232 def = "empty";
233 goto simple;
234 } else if (nb == 1) {
235 def = "very short file (no magic)";
236 goto simple;
237 }
238
239 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_ENCODING) == 0) {
240 looks_text = file_encoding(ms, &b, NULL, 0,
241 &code, &code_mime, &ftype);
242 }
243
244#ifdef __EMX__
245 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_APPTYPE) == 0 && inname) {
246 m = file_os2_apptype(ms, inname, &b);
247 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
248 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try os2_apptype %d]\n", m);
249 switch (m) {
250 case -1:
251 return -1;
252 case 0:
253 break;
254 default:
255 return 1;
256 }
257 }
258#endif
259#if HAVE_FORK
260 /* try compression stuff */
261 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_COMPRESS) == 0) {
262 m = file_zmagic(ms, &b, inname);
263 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
264 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try zmagic %d]\n", m);
265 if (m) {
266 goto done_encoding;
267 }
268 }
269#endif
270 /* Check if we have a tar file */
271 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_TAR) == 0) {
272 m = file_is_tar(ms, &b);
273 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
274 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try tar %d]\n", m);
275 if (m) {
276 if (checkdone(ms, &rv))
277 goto done;
278 }
279 }
280
281 /* Check if we have a JSON file */
282 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_JSON) == 0) {
283 m = file_is_json(ms, &b);
284 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
285 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try json %d]\n", m);
286 if (m) {
287 if (checkdone(ms, &rv))
288 goto done;
289 }
290 }
291
292 /* Check if we have a CDF file */
293 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_CDF) == 0) {
294 m = file_trycdf(ms, &b);
295 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
296 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try cdf %d]\n", m);
297 if (m) {
298 if (checkdone(ms, &rv))
299 goto done;
300 }
301 }
302#ifdef BUILTIN_ELF
303 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_ELF) == 0 && nb > 5 && fd != -1) {
304 file_pushbuf_t *pb;
305 /*
306 * We matched something in the file, so this
307 * *might* be an ELF file, and the file is at
308 * least 5 bytes long, so if it's an ELF file
309 * it has at least one byte past the ELF magic
310 * number - try extracting information from the
311 * ELF headers that cannot easily be extracted
312 * with rules in the magic file. We we don't
313 * print the information yet.
314 */
315 if ((pb = file_push_buffer(ms)) == NULL)
316 return -1;
317
318 rv = file_tryelf(ms, &b);
319 rbuf = file_pop_buffer(ms, pb);
320 if (rv == -1) {
321 free(rbuf);
322 rbuf = NULL;
323 }
324 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
325 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try elf %d]\n", m);
326 }
327#endif
328
329 /* try soft magic tests */
330 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_SOFT) == 0) {
331 m = file_softmagic(ms, &b, NULL, NULL, BINTEST, looks_text);
332 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
333 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try softmagic %d]\n", m);
334 if (m == 1 && rbuf) {
335 if (file_printf(ms, "%s", rbuf) == -1)
336 goto done;
337 }
338 if (m) {
339 if (checkdone(ms, &rv))
340 goto done;
341 }
342 }
343
344 /* try text properties */
345 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_NO_CHECK_TEXT) == 0) {
346
347 m = file_ascmagic(ms, &b, looks_text);
348 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_DEBUG) != 0)
349 (void)fprintf(stderr, "[try ascmagic %d]\n", m);
350 if (m) {
351 goto done;
352 }
353 }
354
355simple:
356 /* give up */
357 if (m == 0) {
358 m = 1;
359 rv = file_default(ms, nb);
360 if (rv == 0)
361 if (file_printf(ms, "%s", def) == -1)
362 rv = -1;
363 }
364 done:
365 if ((ms->flags & MAGIC_MIME_ENCODING) != 0) {
366 if (ms->flags & MAGIC_MIME_TYPE)
367 if (file_printf(ms, "; charset=") == -1)
368 rv = -1;
369 if (file_printf(ms, "%s", code_mime) == -1)
370 rv = -1;
371 }
372#if HAVE_FORK
373 done_encoding:
374#endif
375 free(rbuf);
376 buffer_fini(&b);
377 if (rv)
378 return rv;
379
380 return m;
381}
382#endif

384protected int
385file_reset(struct magic_set *ms, int checkloaded)
386{
387 if (checkloaded && ms->mlist[0] == NULL) {
388 file_error(ms, 0, "no magic files loaded");
389 return -1;
390 }
391 if (ms->o.buf) {
392 free(ms->o.buf);
393 ms->o.buf = NULL;
394 }
395 if (ms->o.pbuf) {
396 free(ms->o.pbuf);
397 ms->o.pbuf = NULL;
398 }
399 ms->event_flags &= ~EVENT_HAD_ERR;
400 ms->error = -1;
401 return 0;
402}
403
404#define OCTALIFY(n, o) \
405 /*LINTED*/ \
406 (void)(*(n)++ = '\\', \
407 *(n)++ = ((CAST(uint32_t, *(o)) >> 6) & 3) + '0', \
408 *(n)++ = ((CAST(uint32_t, *(o)) >> 3) & 7) + '0', \
409 *(n)++ = ((CAST(uint32_t, *(o)) >> 0) & 7) + '0', \
410 (o)++)
411
412protected const char *
413file_getbuffer(struct magic_set *ms)
414{
415 char *pbuf, *op, *np;
416 size_t psize, len;
417
418 if (ms->event_flags & EVENT_HAD_ERR)
419 return NULL;
420
421 if (ms->flags & MAGIC_RAW)
422 return ms->o.buf;
423
424 if (ms->o.buf == NULL)
425 return NULL;
426
427 /* * 4 is for octal representation, + 1 is for NUL */
428 len = strlen(ms->o.buf);
429 if (len > (SIZE_MAX - 1) / 4) {
430 file_oomem(ms, len);
431 return NULL;
432 }
433 psize = len * 4 + 1;
434 if ((pbuf = CAST(char *, realloc(ms->o.pbuf, psize))) == NULL) {
435 file_oomem(ms, psize);
436 return NULL;
437 }
438 ms->o.pbuf = pbuf;
439
440#if defined(HAVE_WCHAR_H) && defined(HAVE_MBRTOWC) && defined(HAVE_WCWIDTH)
441 {
442 mbstate_t state;
443 wchar_t nextchar;
444 int mb_conv = 1;
445 size_t bytesconsumed;
446 char *eop;
447 (void)memset(&state, 0, sizeof(mbstate_t));
448
449 np = ms->o.pbuf;
450 op = ms->o.buf;
451 eop = op + len;
452
453 while (op < eop) {
454 bytesconsumed = mbrtowc(&nextchar, op,
455 CAST(size_t, eop - op), &state);
456 if (bytesconsumed == CAST(size_t, -1) ||
457 bytesconsumed == CAST(size_t, -2)) {
458 mb_conv = 0;
459 break;
460 }
461
462 if (iswprint(nextchar)) {
463 (void)memcpy(np, op, bytesconsumed);
464 op += bytesconsumed;
465 np += bytesconsumed;
466 } else {
467 while (bytesconsumed-- > 0)
468 OCTALIFY(np, op);
469 }
470 }
471 *np = '\0';
472
473 /* Parsing succeeded as a multi-byte sequence */
474 if (mb_conv != 0)
475 return ms->o.pbuf;
476 }
477#endif
478
479 for (np = ms->o.pbuf, op = ms->o.buf; *op;) {
480 if (isprint(CAST(unsigned char, *op))) {
481 *np++ = *op++;
482 } else {
483 OCTALIFY(np, op);
484 }
485 }
486 *np = '\0';
487 return ms->o.pbuf;
488}
489
490protected int
491file_check_mem(struct magic_set *ms, unsigned int level)
492{
493 size_t len;
494
495 if (level >= ms->c.len) {
496 len = (ms->c.len = 20 + level) * sizeof(*ms->c.li);
497 ms->c.li = CAST(struct level_info *, (ms->c.li == NULL) ?
498 malloc(len) :
499 realloc(ms->c.li, len));
500 if (ms->c.li == NULL) {
501 file_oomem(ms, len);
502 return -1;
503 }
504 }
505 ms->c.li[level].got_match = 0;
506#ifdef ENABLE_CONDITIONALS
507 ms->c.li[level].last_match = 0;
508 ms->c.li[level].last_cond = COND_NONE;
509#endif /* ENABLE_CONDITIONALS */
510 return 0;
511}

513protected size_t
514file_printedlen(const struct magic_set *ms)
515{
516 return ms->o.buf == NULL ? 0 : strlen(ms->o.buf);
517}
518
519protected int
520file_replace(struct magic_set *ms, const char *pat, const char *rep)
521{
522 file_regex_t rx;
523 int rc, rv = -1;
524
525 rc = file_regcomp(&rx, pat, REG_EXTENDED);
526 if (rc) {
527 file_regerror(&rx, rc, ms);
528 } else {
529 regmatch_t rm;
530 int nm = 0;
531 while (file_regexec(&rx, ms->o.buf, 1, &rm, 0) == 0) {
532 ms->o.buf[rm.rm_so] = '\0';
533 if (file_printf(ms, "%s%s", rep,
534 rm.rm_eo != 0 ? ms->o.buf + rm.rm_eo : "") == -1)
535 goto out;
536 nm++;
537 }
538 rv = nm;
539 }
540out:
541 file_regfree(&rx);
542 return rv;
543}
544
545protected int
546file_regcomp(file_regex_t *rx, const char *pat, int flags)
547{
548#ifdef USE_C_LOCALE
549 rx->c_lc_ctype = newlocale(LC_CTYPE_MASK, "C", 0);
550 assert(rx->c_lc_ctype != NULL);
551 rx->old_lc_ctype = uselocale(rx->c_lc_ctype);
552 assert(rx->old_lc_ctype != NULL);
553#else
554 rx->old_lc_ctype = setlocale(LC_CTYPE, "C");
555#endif
556 rx->pat = pat;
557
558 return rx->rc = regcomp(&rx->rx, pat, flags);
559}
560
561protected int
562file_regexec(file_regex_t *rx, const char *str, size_t nmatch,
563 regmatch_t* pmatch, int eflags)
564{
565 assert(rx->rc == 0);
566 /* XXX: force initialization because glibc does not always do this */
567 memset(pmatch, 0, nmatch * sizeof(*pmatch));
568 return regexec(&rx->rx, str, nmatch, pmatch, eflags);
569}
570
571protected void
572file_regfree(file_regex_t *rx)
573{
574 if (rx->rc == 0)
575 regfree(&rx->rx);
576#ifdef USE_C_LOCALE
577 (void)uselocale(rx->old_lc_ctype);
578 freelocale(rx->c_lc_ctype);
579#else
580 (void)setlocale(LC_CTYPE, rx->old_lc_ctype);
581#endif
582}
583
584protected void
585file_regerror(file_regex_t *rx, int rc, struct magic_set *ms)
586{
587 char errmsg[512];
588
589 (void)regerror(rc, &rx->rx, errmsg, sizeof(errmsg));
590 file_magerror(ms, "regex error %d for `%s', (%s)", rc, rx->pat,
591 errmsg);
592}
593
594protected file_pushbuf_t *
595file_push_buffer(struct magic_set *ms)
596{
597 file_pushbuf_t *pb;
598
599 if (ms->event_flags & EVENT_HAD_ERR)
600 return NULL;
601
602 if ((pb = (CAST(file_pushbuf_t *, malloc(sizeof(*pb))))) == NULL)
603 return NULL;
604
605 pb->buf = ms->o.buf;
606 pb->offset = ms->offset;
607
608 ms->o.buf = NULL;
609 ms->offset = 0;
610
611 return pb;
612}
613
614protected char *
615file_pop_buffer(struct magic_set *ms, file_pushbuf_t *pb)
616{
617 char *rbuf;
618
619 if (ms->event_flags & EVENT_HAD_ERR) {
620 free(pb->buf);
621 free(pb);
622 return NULL;
623 }
624
625 rbuf = ms->o.buf;
626
627 ms->o.buf = pb->buf;
628 ms->offset = pb->offset;
629
630 free(pb);
631 return rbuf;
632}
633
634/*
635 * convert string to ascii printable format.
636 */
637protected char *
638file_printable(char *buf, size_t bufsiz, const char *str, size_t slen)
639{
640 char *ptr, *eptr = buf + bufsiz - 1;
641 const unsigned char *s = RCAST(const unsigned char *, str);
642 const unsigned char *es = s + slen;
643
644 for (ptr = buf; ptr < eptr && s < es && *s; s++) {
645 if (isprint(*s)) {
646 *ptr++ = *s;
647 continue;
648 }
649 if (ptr >= eptr - 3)
650 break;
651 *ptr++ = '\\';
652 *ptr++ = ((CAST(unsigned int, *s) >> 6) & 7) + '0';
653 *ptr++ = ((CAST(unsigned int, *s) >> 3) & 7) + '0';
654 *ptr++ = ((CAST(unsigned int, *s) >> 0) & 7) + '0';
655 }
656 *ptr = '\0';
657 return buf;
658}
